x_{1},x_{2},y_{1},y_{2}\in\mathbb{R}
\left|x_{1}\right|\ge\left|x_{2}\right|
\left|y_{1}\right|\ge\left|y_{2}\right|
\left|\left|x_{1}\right|-\left|y_{1}\right|\right|+\left|\left|x_{2}\right|-\left|y_{2}\right|\right|\le\left|x_{1}-y_{2}\right|+\left|x_{2}-y_{1}\right| 
|x_{1}-y_{1}|+|x_{2}-y_{2}|\le|x_{1}-y_{2}|+|x_{2}-y_{1}|\ (*) 
x_1 \leq y_1
